With over 70 different species of grass, Grasslands National Park has an important role to play in protecting the prairie ecosystem. 🌾 🌾 🌾  The grasses are the heart and soul of the prairies and without them, you wouldn’t be able to see the buffalo roam and the deer and the antelope play. 📷: @paulmlbr
